# Digital Alarm Clock (Verilog HDL)

## Overview

This project implements a modular Digital Alarm Clock in Verilog HDL using a hierarchical RTL design approach. The design displays the current time, allows the user to set the current time and alarm time, compares the current time with the programmed alarm, and activates an alarm when the programmed time is reached.

The project was developed to practice RTL design, finite state machines (FSMs), modular design methodology, and functional verification using simulation.

---

## Features

- 24-hour digital clock
- Real-time seconds, minutes, and hours counters
- Adjustable current time
- Adjustable alarm time
- Alarm enable/disable functionality
- Alarm comparison logic
- Finite State Machine (FSM) based operating modes
- Button edge detection for reliable user input
- Fully modular RTL implementation
- Functional verification using a Verilog testbench

---

## Operating Modes

The clock operates in four modes:

### 1. Show Time
- Displays the current running time
- Clock increments automatically every second

### 2. Set Time
- Freezes the clock
- Allows manual adjustment of hours and minutes

### 3. Set Alarm
- Allows programming of the alarm time
- Alarm can be enabled or disabled

### 4. Alarm Ringing
- Triggered when the current time matches the programmed alarm time
- Alarm remains active until stopped by the user

---

## Project Architecture

```
                   +----------------+
                   | Clock Divider  |
                   +-------+--------+
                           |
                           v
                  +------------------+
                  | Seconds Counter  |
                  +--------+---------+
                           |
                           v
                  +------------------+
                  | Minutes Counter  |
                  +--------+---------+
                           |
                           v
                  +------------------+
                  |  Hours Counter   |
                  +--------+---------+
                           |
                Current Time (HH:MM:SS)
                           |
                           |
         +-----------------+----------------+
         |                                  |
         v                                  v
 +-------------------+          +-------------------+
 | Alarm Register    |          | Alarm Comparator  |
 +-------------------+          +---------+---------+
                                           |
                                           v
                                   Alarm Match Signal
                                           |
                                           v
                                 +-------------------+
                                 | FSM Controller    |
                                 +-------------------+
                                           |
         --------------------------------------------------------
         |                |               |                     |
         v                v               v                     v
   Clock Enable     Set Time Mode   Set Alarm Mode     Buzzer Enable
```

---

## RTL Modules

| Module | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `clock_divider` | Generates a 1 Hz tick from the system clock (simulation divisor used for verification). |
| `seconds_counter` | Counts seconds from 0–59. |
| `minutes_counter` | Counts minutes from 0–59 and handles carry generation. |
| `hour_counter` | Counts hours from 0–23 and handles day rollover. |
| `alarm_register` | Stores programmable alarm hour and minute. |
| `alarm_comparator` | Compares current time with programmed alarm time. |
| `fsm_controller` | Controls operating modes using a Moore FSM. |
| `button_edge_detector` | Generates a single pulse for every button press. |
| `digital_alarm_clock` | Top-level module integrating all submodules. |

---

## FSM States

| State | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| SHOW_TIME | Normal clock operation |
| SET_TIME | User adjusts current time |
| SET_ALARM | User programs alarm |
| ALARM_RINGING | Alarm active until stopped |

---

## Verification

The project was verified using a comprehensive Verilog testbench covering:

- Reset functionality
- Normal clock operation
- Time setting
- Alarm programming
- Alarm enable/disable
- FSM state transitions
- Alarm trigger
- Alarm stop functionality
- Counter rollover conditions

Simulation was performed using **Xilinx Vivado Simulator (XSim)**.

---

## Design Concepts Demonstrated

- Register Transfer Level (RTL) Design
- Hierarchical Design Methodology
- Finite State Machines (FSM)
- Clock Enable Based Design
- Parameterized Counters
- Combinational and Sequential Logic
- Edge Detection
- Modular Verification
- Functional Simulation

